<html>
  <%= render 'shared/header', stylesheet_link: 'pages', page_title: "Help" %>
	<head>
		<style>
		
			table, th, td {
			border: 1px solid black;
			}
			table.center {
			margin-left: auto;
			margin-right: auto;
			}
			
			.button {
				background-color: #4CAF50; /* Green */
				border: none;
				color: white;
				padding: 15px 32px;
				text-align: center;
				text-decoration: none;
				display: inline-block;
				font-size: 16px;
				margin: 4px 2px;
				cursor: pointer;
				border-radius: 12px;
				box-shadow: 0 12px 16px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.24), 0 17px 50px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.19);
			}
			
		</style>
	</head>
	
	<body>
	  <%= render 'shared/navbar' %>
	  <div class="help-title">
			
			<h2>Add Player Statistics:</h2>
			<p>
			To add player statistics, you will need to start from the Players page. Next, 
			you will need to find the specific player that you want to give statistics. 
			After finding the desired player, you will need to click the blue "Edit/Create Stats"
			button.
			</p>
			
			
			<%= image_tag("add_stats1.png", size:"500x250") %>
			
			<p>
			This will direct you to a page similar to the one seen below. It is here where you will need
			to navigate through the calendar in order to find the game that the player participated in. Next,
			you will need to click the blue "Select" button on the game card.
			</p>
			
			<%= image_tag("add_stats2.png", size:"500x250") %>
			
			<p>
			You should have been directed to the page seen below where you can add all of the player statistics 
			for the given game. Once you are finished, click the green "Create Participation" as seen below. 
			</p>
			
			<%= image_tag("add_stats3.png", size:"500x250") %>
			
			<p>
			You should now be on the page seen below where you can confirm your changes.
			</p>
			
			<%= image_tag("add_stats4.png", size:"500x250") %>
			
			<br>
			<br>
			
		</div>
	
	<%= render 'shared/footer' %>
<html>
